snippet.title: Amber Scorah: Leaving the Jehovah's Witnesses
snippet.description:
"No one in a cult ever thinks that they are in a cult. They think they are living their best life. Having all the answers to life's questions is really relaxing. The world is ending, armageddon and God is going to solve all problems." 

Amber Scorah is the author of the moving memoir "Leaving the Witness," which details her experience growing up in the Jehovahâ€™s Witness faith, moving to China to become a missionary, coming to question the beliefs she had been taught, and eventually leaving the religion. After suffering the tragic loss of her three-month-old son, Amber became a parental leave advocate, bringing this issue to the forefront of the 2016 campaign. 

Learn more about the Freedom From Religion Foundation at ffrf.org.
